Description: Handle of pottery transport amphora. Circular(?) stamp; 'bull's head, full face'.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's words in his Journal, 1884-5, p.32, 15. It may well be that this entry is to be taken with 32, 10, to make one Knidian stamp.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1737)
